WEBVTT

1
00:03:11.776 --> 00:03:14.376
- Only one. Only one!
- That's enough. Stand back.

2
00:03:21.244 --> 00:03:22.328
Behold!

3
00:03:23.413 --> 00:03:26.207
The traitor dragon Meleys!

4
00:03:26.290 --> 00:03:27.875
- Where?
- Look.

5
00:03:27.959 --> 00:03:31.712
Slain at Rook's Rest by your king!

6
00:03:34.507 --> 00:03:35.550
To Aegon!

7
00:03:38.261 --> 00:03:39.262
Can't be...

8
00:03:44.684 --> 00:03:46.310
He killed a dragon.

9
00:03:48.020 --> 00:03:50.231
Mark my words.
This is a black omen.

10
00:04:08.666 --> 00:04:10.418
Rhaenyra will answer this.

11
00:04:12.170 --> 00:04:13.629
It is an abomination!

12
00:04:15.006 --> 00:04:17.091
Don't they realize we won the battle?

13
00:04:18.301 --> 00:04:19.427
Strange victory.

14
00:04:21.220 --> 00:04:22.680
If it was one.

15
00:04:41.199 --> 00:04:42.200
Behold!

16
00:04:43.659 --> 00:04:46.412
The traitor dragon Meleys!

17
00:04:46.496 --> 00:04:48.039
I thought the dragons was gods.

18
00:04:48.122 --> 00:04:51.501
Slain at Rook's Rest
by your king!

19
00:04:59.884 --> 00:05:00.968
It's just meat.

20
00:05:02.970 --> 00:05:05.389
Get back. Stay back.

21
00:07:21.192 --> 00:07:22.443
Is he alive?

22
00:07:22.526 --> 00:07:27.281
His Grace remains with us for the moment.

23
00:08:24.296 --> 00:08:25.506
Is my son going to die?

24
00:08:25.589 --> 00:08:27.466
I'm afraid I cannot say.

25
00:08:27.550 --> 00:08:30.886
Now. if you'll excuse me. Your Grace.
these next hours are most critical.

26
00:08:30.970 --> 00:08:31.971
Of course.

27
00:08:44.817 --> 00:08:46.652
Easy as you can.

28
00:09:06.839 --> 00:09:09.258
Someone will have to rule in his stead.

29
00:09:33.115 --> 00:09:34.158
What happened?

30
00:09:34.241 --> 00:09:37.703
We took the castle.
At the cost of some 900 men.

31
00:09:40.164 --> 00:09:41.248
So I've heard.

32
00:09:43.542 --> 00:09:47.254
I left a meager garrison behind
to protect it. And the king's dragon.

33
00:09:48.547 --> 00:09:50.382
Sunfyre was long in the dying.

34
00:09:51.258 --> 00:09:53.594
The king. Ser Criston. What befell him?

35
00:09:57.473 --> 00:09:59.183
His Grace fought valiantly.

36
00:10:05.981 --> 00:10:06.982
And Aemond?

37
00:10:14.406 --> 00:10:15.699
What was his part in this?

38
00:10:20.371 --> 00:10:21.455
I could not say.

39
00:10:26.126 --> 00:10:28.420
Our largest dragon
has been killed.

40
00:10:29.839 --> 00:10:33.634
Criston Cole marches about
the Crownlands. unchallenged.

41
00:10:34.552 --> 00:10:37.513
Duskendale and Rook's Rest are gone.

42
00:10:38.973 --> 00:10:42.601
We still have no ground army but the one
we hope that Daemon will raise.

43
00:10:43.394 --> 00:10:47.690
He who has left us
after some marital spat.

44
00:10:50.067 --> 00:10:51.652
Do you take issue with me. Ser Alfred?

45
00:10:54.446 --> 00:10:56.574
My loyalty to you is proven. my queen.

46
00:10:56.657 --> 00:10:58.242
Your loyalty. perhaps.

47
00:10:58.951 --> 00:11:01.704
But your willingness
to give me deference in a time of war?

48
00:11:01.787 --> 00:11:07.001
I could never doubt your capability
or your quickness of mind.

49
00:11:08.961 --> 00:11:10.838
It is merely that the gentler sex

50
00:11:10.921 --> 00:11:15.384
heretofore has not been much privy
to the strategies of battle.

51
00:11:16.135 --> 00:11:17.469
Or their execution.

52
00:11:19.722 --> 00:11:23.559
There has been peace in our lifetime.
You've seen no more battles than I have.

53
00:11:43.913 --> 00:11:46.540
Send to Maidenpool and to Crackclaw Point.

54
00:11:46.624 --> 00:11:49.084
Let them man their garrisons.
and give them stores or weapons

55
00:11:49.168 --> 00:11:50.419
if they find them wanting.

56
00:11:51.921 --> 00:11:54.423
If Cole pursues his campaign.
our allies must be ready.

57
00:11:54.506 --> 00:11:57.635
We must answer Rook's Rest.
And Duskendale.

58
00:11:57.718 --> 00:12:02.640
They are lost already. But Vhagar is
depleted after such a hard-fought battle.

59
00:12:02.723 --> 00:12:05.267
- If Aegon is dead...
- We will soon know it.

60
00:12:05.351 --> 00:12:07.120
'Twould will be a victory
in name only.

61
00:12:07.144 --> 00:12:09.021
They will soon prop up another
in his stead.

62
00:12:09.104 --> 00:12:10.731
The time is ripe.

63
00:12:10.814 --> 00:12:13.454
If we can strike King's Landing
before their dragon is recovered...

64
00:12:13.484 --> 00:12:15.277
Then I. myself. must do it.

65
00:12:15.361 --> 00:12:18.822
My queen. you are the crown.
It is out of the question.

66
00:12:18.906 --> 00:12:20.574
What would you have me do?

67
00:12:41.971 --> 00:12:43.013
Jace?

68
00:12:46.433 --> 00:12:47.643
Where are you going?

69
00:12:49.311 --> 00:12:50.312
To Harrenhal.

70
00:12:51.522 --> 00:12:52.773
To treat with Daemon.

71
00:12:53.399 --> 00:12:54.817
Rhaenys is fallen.

72
00:12:54.900 --> 00:12:58.153
He must affirm his loyalty to my mother
and report his standing.

73
00:13:01.448 --> 00:13:05.536
And you think you will tame him
when the queen herself could not?

74
00:13:05.619 --> 00:13:07.663
My mother gladly sends you away.

75
00:13:08.330 --> 00:13:10.374
To scout. to fight.

76
00:13:10.457 --> 00:13:13.627
whilst I'm here being forced
to play the coddled princeling.

77
00:13:13.711 --> 00:13:15.379
It's humiliating. Baela.

78
00:13:15.462 --> 00:13:19.341
She only protects you.
You are the succession.

79
00:13:19.425 --> 00:13:23.137
Then I must be seen
to act for her claim and mine.

80
00:13:27.182 --> 00:13:28.851
I can sit still no longer.

81
00:13:32.146 --> 00:13:33.188
I must act.

82
00:13:41.530 --> 00:13:42.531
The Freys.

83
00:13:44.742 --> 00:13:46.702
They control the crossing at the Twins.

84
00:13:47.327 --> 00:13:49.955
Cregan Stark's graybeards
are marching south.

85
00:13:50.039 --> 00:13:53.000
If his men had a direct route
into the Riverlands.

86
00:13:53.584 --> 00:13:56.086
we would not have to wait
for Daemon to act.

87
00:13:56.170 --> 00:13:58.297
I will treat with the Freys to secure it.

88
00:13:58.964 --> 00:14:00.257
She will not like it.

89
00:14:01.341 --> 00:14:04.386
Then don't tell her. Not until I'm away.

90
00:14:18.400 --> 00:14:21.528
The hour is late
and my dragon is hungry.

91
00:14:22.321 --> 00:14:24.281
You have no choice but to submit.

92
00:14:24.990 --> 00:14:26.742
Our terms are simple. Lord Bracken.

93
00:14:26.825 --> 00:14:29.661
Renounce the false king Aegon
as a usurper

94
00:14:30.579 --> 00:14:31.914
and bend the knee to me...

95
00:14:33.332 --> 00:14:35.084
or your house burns.

96
00:14:35.167 --> 00:14:38.295
I would sooner be the lord
of bones and cinders

97
00:14:38.378 --> 00:14:44.259
than bend my knee before some heathen
Blackwood cunt and his hired dragon.

98
00:14:44.343 --> 00:14:46.404
The Brackens were a people
hatched out of the deepest

99
00:14:46.428 --> 00:14:48.347
of the Seven Hells. Your Grace.

100
00:14:48.430 --> 00:14:51.725
It would be a kindness to oblige them
and send them back whence they came.

101
00:14:51.809 --> 00:14:55.104
Did your brother's head keep
on its way back to you. Willem?

102
00:14:55.979 --> 00:14:57.815
I heard the maggots got to it.

103
00:14:57.898 --> 00:15:00.400
That is quite the impression.
Lord Bracken.

104
00:15:01.693 --> 00:15:03.487
but alas. not an answer.

105
00:15:13.539 --> 00:15:14.957
We choose fire.

106
00:15:25.759 --> 00:15:28.428
I did not think
they would be so eager to die.

107
00:15:30.013 --> 00:15:33.392
They made their choice.
You should have indulged them.

108
00:15:33.475 --> 00:15:37.479
I need them alive. I came here
to raise swords. not corpses.

109
00:15:38.814 --> 00:15:41.859
But now you see what my house
has known for generations.

110
00:15:41.942 --> 00:15:44.403
They are pig-headed. intransigent...

111
00:15:44.486 --> 00:15:46.321
They would rather burn than succumb.

112
00:15:50.284 --> 00:15:52.161
Exactly the kind of men I need.

113
00:15:54.454 --> 00:15:57.916
It may yet be possible. I think.
for both of us to achieve our ends.

114
00:15:58.000 --> 00:16:00.085
We have fought them for an age and more.

115
00:16:01.170 --> 00:16:04.173
Then perhaps you could try
less fighting and more...

116
00:16:08.010 --> 00:16:09.094
persuading.

117
00:16:10.846 --> 00:16:12.806
They are unyielding in battle.

118
00:16:20.272 --> 00:16:21.940
But every man has a weakness.

119
00:16:23.275 --> 00:16:24.818
You take my meaning. then.

120
00:16:29.239 --> 00:16:32.701
There are things the crown itself
must not be seen to do.

121
00:16:34.661 --> 00:16:37.998
- Show them your worst.
- I am your servant. Your Grace.

122
00:16:59.978 --> 00:17:01.396
<i>Over the centuries.</i>

123
00:17:02.105 --> 00:17:04.650
<i>many and more armies
have broken themselves</i>

124
00:17:04.733 --> 00:17:06.443
against my Bloody Gate.

125
00:17:10.948 --> 00:17:12.115
Are you listening?

126
00:17:13.951 --> 00:17:14.952
My lady?

127
00:17:15.702 --> 00:17:17.704
The Eyrie itself is impregnable.

128
00:17:20.749 --> 00:17:23.961
Unless. of course.
we're descended upon from the sky.

129
00:17:24.044 --> 00:17:26.672
You promised the queen Rhaenyra
15.000 swords...

130
00:17:26.755 --> 00:17:29.466
In return for protection. A dragon.

131
00:17:31.635 --> 00:17:35.389
Then she has exceeded your terms.
She sent two.

132
00:17:36.223 --> 00:17:38.016
Both still wet from the egg.

133
00:17:40.310 --> 00:17:42.729
I have hunting hounds
that are more fearsome.

134
00:17:42.813 --> 00:17:44.648
They are dragons nonetheless.

135
00:17:45.649 --> 00:17:48.777
I do not recall you specifying
the size of the beast in your request.

136
00:17:48.860 --> 00:17:50.320
Will you goad me. child.

137
00:17:51.363 --> 00:17:54.074
when your bread and shelter
now depend on my pleasure?

138
00:17:55.951 --> 00:17:57.286
The dragons will grow.

139
00:17:58.954 --> 00:18:00.622
- In time.
- I don't have time.

140
00:18:02.916 --> 00:18:04.626
I mislike feeling powerless.

141
00:18:06.586 --> 00:18:07.587
So do I.

142
00:18:14.553 --> 00:18:18.473
This will be your chamber.
I'll expect you at supper this evening.

143
00:18:21.643 --> 00:18:24.896
My sympathies for the death
of your grandmother.

144
00:18:33.947 --> 00:18:36.992
The way they spoke
at my Small Council today...

145
00:18:37.075 --> 00:18:40.370
Do they hold you responsible
for Rhaenys and her dragon?

146
00:18:40.454 --> 00:18:44.791
I would rather they had.
They speak around me. not to me.

147
00:18:46.293 --> 00:18:49.421
They would make me queen.
but they wish to keep me here. confined.

148
00:18:49.504 --> 00:18:51.757
They betray their own smallness.

149
00:18:52.507 --> 00:18:56.219
In truth. I cannot fault them. I am now
the sovereign. I cannot do as I please.

150
00:18:58.013 --> 00:19:00.849
And war has ever been for men to make.

151
00:19:00.932 --> 00:19:03.602
You are your father's chosen successor.

152
00:19:04.311 --> 00:19:06.521
He did not prepare me to fight.

153
00:19:06.605 --> 00:19:10.150
If I had been a son.
a sword thrust into my hand

154
00:19:10.233 --> 00:19:11.777
the moment I could walk...

155
00:19:12.903 --> 00:19:17.991
Instead. I was given my father's cup.
taught the name of every lord and castle

156
00:19:18.075 --> 00:19:19.868
between Storm's End and the Twins.

157
00:19:19.951 --> 00:19:22.746
but not the difference
between hilt and foible.

158
00:19:23.705 --> 00:19:24.873
And they know it.

159
00:19:26.833 --> 00:19:27.876
And Daemon as well.

160
00:19:27.959 --> 00:19:30.337
Shall your evening meal
be served here. Your Grace?

161
00:19:30.420 --> 00:19:31.797
Not now.

162
00:19:38.136 --> 00:19:39.679
Will you send to him?

163
00:19:41.181 --> 00:19:43.558
For too long I have looked to him
for strength.

164
00:19:44.476 --> 00:19:47.270
If I must be supplicant to my own husband.
what does that make me?

165
00:19:51.441 --> 00:19:54.111
I do not know my part. Mysaria.

166
00:19:57.656 --> 00:19:59.449
The path I walk has never been trod.

167
00:20:01.535 --> 00:20:04.079
Criston Cole made a mistake.

168
00:20:06.706 --> 00:20:10.752
Parading a dragon's head
through the streets like a prize of war.

169
00:20:10.836 --> 00:20:13.130
But the people see an ill omen.

170
00:20:13.213 --> 00:20:14.464
Yes. as do I.

171
00:20:14.548 --> 00:20:19.261
They are afraid. bread is scarce.
the king has fallen.

172
00:20:19.344 --> 00:20:22.848
They whisper to each other that
when Viserys lived. there was peace.

173
00:20:22.931 --> 00:20:28.353
But will whispers tear down stone
or break shields?

174
00:20:28.437 --> 00:20:31.606
Do not underestimate your subjects.

175
00:20:31.690 --> 00:20:33.608
They are a thousand thousand

176
00:20:33.692 --> 00:20:37.696
living in the shadow of the Red Keep
and forgotten for too long.

177
00:20:38.530 --> 00:20:40.323
And you think they will turn to me?

178
00:20:40.907 --> 00:20:44.661
To the discontented. rumors are feed.

179
00:20:49.624 --> 00:20:50.834
Your Grace.

180
00:20:53.879 --> 00:20:58.008
What you cannot do. let others do for you.

181
00:20:59.384 --> 00:21:02.012
There is more than one way to fight a war.

182
00:21:24.993 --> 00:21:29.331
The thought of her lying in a field.
broken amongst her enemies...

183
00:21:40.800 --> 00:21:44.137
Did your grandmother ever tell you
of the night she claimed Meleys?

184
00:21:45.847 --> 00:21:47.724
She snuck into the Dragonpit.

185
00:21:48.642 --> 00:21:53.188
She knew that place better than any Elder.
They say she could see in the dark.

186
00:21:55.232 --> 00:21:58.944
My father was furious.
His own mother's dragon.

187
00:21:59.027 --> 00:22:01.780
The fastest beast ever known.
and she'd have none of him.

188
00:22:01.863 --> 00:22:04.449
But bent her neck to Rhaenys.

189
00:22:05.992 --> 00:22:07.285
She was fierce.

190
00:22:09.329 --> 00:22:10.830
In love and in anger.

191
00:22:14.042 --> 00:22:15.919
She did not always care for me.

192
00:22:16.795 --> 00:22:21.216
But... for what she gave me in the end.

193
00:22:22.300 --> 00:22:23.343
I'm grateful.

194
00:22:29.558 --> 00:22:31.601
I wish I had known her
when she was young.

195
00:22:39.109 --> 00:22:41.570
You are very like her in some ways.

196
00:22:45.031 --> 00:22:46.324
And with her gone.

197
00:22:47.576 --> 00:22:49.744
I must rely on you. I think.

198
00:22:49.828 --> 00:22:51.871
Your Grace?

199
00:22:52.664 --> 00:22:54.291
Would you give this to your grandsire?

200
00:23:06.803 --> 00:23:08.513
I do not wish to stand alone.

201
00:23:12.976 --> 00:23:14.185
<i>Daemon.</i>

202
00:23:19.107 --> 00:23:20.108
<i>Daemon.</i>

203
00:23:21.860 --> 00:23:23.862
<i>You were always the strong one.</i>

204
00:23:26.364 --> 00:23:28.199
The finest swordsman.

205
00:23:31.828 --> 00:23:34.080
The fearless dragonrider.

206
00:23:36.249 --> 00:23:39.502
<i>Your brother had great love in his heart.</i>

207
00:23:44.341 --> 00:23:46.551
<i>But he lacked your constitution.</i>

208
00:23:47.636 --> 00:23:50.138
Viserys wasn't suited for the crown.

209
00:23:53.475 --> 00:23:57.312
<i>But you...
Daemon. you were made to wear it.</i>

210
00:24:17.666 --> 00:24:19.918
<i>If only you'd been born first.</i>

211
00:24:22.003 --> 00:24:23.713
My favorite son.

212
00:24:30.720 --> 00:24:33.306
Is the duck not to your liking.
Your Grace?

213
00:24:39.270 --> 00:24:41.940
There's also goose if you prefer it.

214
00:24:44.234 --> 00:24:45.735
I like the goose myself.

215
00:24:54.452 --> 00:24:55.495
Uh. I'm not hungry.

216
00:24:56.162 --> 00:24:59.541
I was saying. given the rather dire news
from Rook's Rest.

217
00:25:01.209 --> 00:25:05.171
it appears the winds have shifted
and each side has suffered great loss.

218
00:25:05.255 --> 00:25:08.049
and will be unsure of what is to follow.

219
00:25:09.884 --> 00:25:12.053
A good time then for a show of strength.

220
00:25:12.887 --> 00:25:15.890
I believe Willem Blackwood
is bringing House Bracken to heel.

221
00:25:17.809 --> 00:25:20.437
We must ready the castle
to receive a great host.

222
00:25:23.440 --> 00:25:25.150
You seem sure of this.

223
00:25:25.233 --> 00:25:29.028
All men may be led. Ser Simon.
Even Rivermen.

224
00:25:30.864 --> 00:25:33.742
It is a matter of showing them
whom it behooves them to follow.

225
00:25:36.035 --> 00:25:37.620
How does the work here progress?

226
00:25:38.496 --> 00:25:39.622
Oh. Um...

227
00:25:40.957 --> 00:25:44.127
We are drawing water for the kitchens
and lighting the forges.

228
00:25:44.210 --> 00:25:46.671
- Very well.
- That is merely the beginning. of course.

229
00:25:47.505 --> 00:25:49.924
The roof alone has needed tending
since the reign of Aenys.

230
00:25:50.008 --> 00:25:52.594
and the storerooms. and...

231
00:25:53.678 --> 00:25:55.555
And the Wailing Tower.

232
00:25:56.681 --> 00:26:00.727
The bats have made the corridors almost
impassible with the quantity of their...

233
00:26:01.978 --> 00:26:03.229
Their shit.

234
00:26:05.565 --> 00:26:10.278
I venture there are smiths and armorers
to be found near Nutton and Riverbend.

235
00:26:10.361 --> 00:26:13.907
Mm. well. send for them. and levy
the farmers from Antlers to High Heart.

236
00:26:14.824 --> 00:26:17.494
Task their huntsmen
to bring us meat and wood.

237
00:26:18.745 --> 00:26:21.581
Um. there is. of course.
the matter of payment.

238
00:26:23.208 --> 00:26:24.209
After the...

239
00:26:24.876 --> 00:26:27.170
The tragedy that befell his father.

240
00:26:28.087 --> 00:26:31.966
Larys transferred his family's wealth
to King's Landing.

241
00:26:33.468 --> 00:26:36.387
Is there any gold left in your coffers?

242
00:26:36.471 --> 00:26:40.809
Enough to keep this small establishment
you see fed and warm.

243
00:26:41.810 --> 00:26:42.811
Relatively.

244
00:26:45.939 --> 00:26:51.861
I... I rather thought Your Grace.
as emissary to the queen.

245
00:26:52.779 --> 00:26:56.658
that perhaps she could provide
the necessary coin.

246
00:26:56.741 --> 00:26:59.244
- If you could only write to her.
- No.

247
00:27:00.328 --> 00:27:04.082
Harrenhal is my command.
I shall guarantee the payment myself.

248
00:27:07.669 --> 00:27:08.753
Up.

249
00:27:11.381 --> 00:27:12.757
Very well. Your Grace.

250
00:27:13.758 --> 00:27:15.844
You should address me as "My King."

251
00:27:17.136 --> 00:27:18.346
But you're the prince.

252
00:27:19.430 --> 00:27:21.558
What would you call
the husband of the queen?

253
00:27:21.641 --> 00:27:23.201
- Well. the king...
- There it is. then.

254
00:27:23.268 --> 00:27:24.394
...consort.

255
00:27:25.979 --> 00:27:28.273
That last bit seems unnecessary.
don't you think?

256
00:27:34.571 --> 00:27:36.739
The armor was Valyrian steel.

257
00:27:36.823 --> 00:27:40.660
But His Grace suffered grievous burns
over much of his body.

258
00:27:41.870 --> 00:27:46.291
He has many broken bones.
I fear there are more injuries within.

259
00:27:47.250 --> 00:27:49.002
Injuries we cannot see.

260
00:27:51.546 --> 00:27:53.965
We are grateful for your works.
Grand Maester.

261
00:27:55.258 --> 00:27:57.302
- Has he woken?
- No.

262
00:27:59.262 --> 00:28:03.850
I must admit.
I am not sure he will ever wake.

263
00:28:03.933 --> 00:28:07.270
I have plied my crafts
to their fullest extents.

264
00:28:07.353 --> 00:28:11.232
Our king's fate lies with the gods now.

265
00:28:22.035 --> 00:28:26.706
A king cannot rule in his sleep.
The realm will have noticed his absence.

266
00:28:27.957 --> 00:28:30.209
Let them hear
of his great deeds at Rook's Rest.

267
00:28:31.669 --> 00:28:35.715
But now we must name a regent
to take his place until he recovers.

268
00:28:38.551 --> 00:28:39.552
Or does not.

269
00:28:41.346 --> 00:28:43.056
A wise strategy. Your Grace.

270
00:28:43.806 --> 00:28:47.060
A regency will assure the people
of the stability of the crown.

271
00:28:50.688 --> 00:28:53.191
Did you have a candidate in mind.
Your Grace?

272
00:28:54.359 --> 00:28:56.079
I myself served in this role
for my husband.

273
00:28:56.152 --> 00:28:58.071
I am well prepared to do it again.

274
00:28:58.154 --> 00:29:00.740
You played your part admirably
in a time of peace. Your Grace.

275
00:29:00.823 --> 00:29:02.742
But circumstances have changed.

276
00:29:03.451 --> 00:29:05.078
And here I had forgotten.

277
00:29:05.161 --> 00:29:07.372
The king does not lack
for heirs.

278
00:29:07.455 --> 00:29:12.085
The obvious choice is
his immediate successor. Prince Aemond.

279
00:29:12.168 --> 00:29:13.628
Agreed.

280
00:29:13.711 --> 00:29:14.879
Aemond is young.

281
00:29:16.714 --> 00:29:19.258
And his lack of restraint
has already cost us dearly.

282
00:29:28.935 --> 00:29:32.814
It is experience
that offers the surest path to security.

283
00:29:32.897 --> 00:29:36.025
Queen Alicent ably shouldered
the duties of the realm

284
00:29:36.109 --> 00:29:37.735
when her husband's health failed him.

285
00:29:37.819 --> 00:29:40.571
Experience is valuable. yes.
but the dowager queen is a woman.

286
00:29:40.655 --> 00:29:42.991
I am no stranger to rule
or to sitting at this council.

287
00:29:43.825 --> 00:29:46.720
Aemond is a fearsome dragonrider.
His skill is best employed in the field.

288
00:29:46.744 --> 00:29:49.288
But my experience is needed here.
at this table.

289
00:29:49.372 --> 00:29:54.085
No offense was meant. Your Grace.
But at a time when we must show strength...

290
00:29:54.168 --> 00:29:55.211
Lord Larys?

291
00:29:57.171 --> 00:29:59.465
I agree. Your Grace.
It must be Prince Aemond.

292
00:30:01.718 --> 00:30:04.053
What would it say if.
in response to Rhaenyra's crowning.

293
00:30:04.137 --> 00:30:06.180
we raised up a woman of our own?

294
00:30:08.766 --> 00:30:09.767
But. um...

295
00:30:12.145 --> 00:30:15.648
But the Hand speaks with the king's voice.
Ser Criston. what say you?

296
00:30:23.114 --> 00:30:24.949
Aemond is the next in line.

297
00:30:27.535 --> 00:30:28.619
It must be him.

298
00:30:33.416 --> 00:30:34.500
It's agreed. then.

299
00:30:57.106 --> 00:30:59.067
What is our standing in the Riverlands?

300
00:31:01.235 --> 00:31:04.906
The banners of House Tully
are in disarray. Your Grace.

301
00:31:05.823 --> 00:31:10.286
Prince Daemon has little hope
of fielding an army of any size. for now.

302
00:31:11.245 --> 00:31:13.557
We would do well to send word
to young Oscar Tully.

303
00:31:13.581 --> 00:31:15.100
It's only a matter of time

304
00:31:15.124 --> 00:31:17.085
before he inherits his grandsire's mantle.

305
00:31:17.668 --> 00:31:21.172
Tell me. Lord Strong.
how I can trust the counsel of a man

306
00:31:21.255 --> 00:31:24.550
who leaves the jewel of the Riverlands
to be plucked by our enemy?

307
00:31:28.971 --> 00:31:31.811
Your brother's host can meet
Daemon. He should quicken his pace

308
00:31:31.849 --> 00:31:34.477
and check the Rivermen
while their banners are in disarray.

309
00:31:34.560 --> 00:31:36.854
I shall send Lord Jason
encouragement.

310
00:31:36.938 --> 00:31:39.690
- What else?
- We might turn our attention

311
00:31:39.774 --> 00:31:42.110
to the smallfolk here in King's Landing.

312
00:31:42.193 --> 00:31:44.612
They have grown weary
of the Sea Snake's blockade.

313
00:31:44.695 --> 00:31:46.155
So have we all.

314
00:31:46.781 --> 00:31:51.077
Many are fleeing the city.
spreading word of their fear and unrest.

315
00:31:51.786 --> 00:31:54.497
Mm. Then let the gates be closed.

316
00:31:57.041 --> 00:32:01.629
No one is to leave or enter. save with
our consent. Merchants. so forth.

317
00:32:06.592 --> 00:32:07.802
Go to your tasks.

318
00:32:09.512 --> 00:32:11.264
We shall meet again at first light.

319
00:32:11.848 --> 00:32:15.017
Oh. and someone cut down
the fucking ratcatchers.

320
00:32:22.775 --> 00:32:24.318
The city's safe no longer.

321
00:32:26.821 --> 00:32:28.030
There is no food.

322
00:32:29.282 --> 00:32:32.535
Our neighbors are stealing
from each other. We must get out.

323
00:32:32.618 --> 00:32:36.330
And where would you have us go?
North. maybe? South?

324
00:32:37.456 --> 00:32:40.001
For all we know.
every road leads into the dragons' teeth.

325
00:32:40.084 --> 00:32:41.844
Like the one they carted
through the streets?

326
00:32:42.670 --> 00:32:46.048
You think Rhaenyra will let
such an affront go unchallenged?

327
00:32:49.468 --> 00:32:54.432
We should make for Tumbleton.
My brother will have room.

328
00:32:54.515 --> 00:32:56.017
You would have me turn beggar.

329
00:33:02.398 --> 00:33:04.025
Are we not beggars already?

330
00:33:05.443 --> 00:33:08.112
Have you been paid for those machines
you were forced to build?

331
00:33:08.196 --> 00:33:12.033
- The king has promised payment.
- The king has lied.

332
00:33:24.253 --> 00:33:29.759
By all means. stay and wait
for his empty promises. husband.

333
00:33:32.470 --> 00:33:34.597
With them. you can feed
the mouths of ghosts.

334
00:34:14.637 --> 00:34:19.642
Presumed you'd be here. Seeing faithfully
to the Prince Regent's commands.

335
00:34:20.434 --> 00:34:23.688
Aemond is the next in line.
It is the order of things.

336
00:34:23.771 --> 00:34:26.691
You know what he is.
What he has somehow become.

337
00:34:30.778 --> 00:34:33.572
Has your loyalty faded.
or does it flourish only at night

338
00:34:33.656 --> 00:34:35.616
and flee the sunrise like a moth?

339
00:34:40.329 --> 00:34:44.542
- What I saw at Rook's Rest...
- What? What did you see?

340
00:34:49.171 --> 00:34:50.506
Their armor melted.

341
00:34:52.842 --> 00:34:54.969
There were men walking. they were on fire.

342
00:34:58.889 --> 00:35:00.766
We have given the war to the dragons.

343
00:35:02.852 --> 00:35:04.312
A dragonrider should lead us.

344
00:35:08.733 --> 00:35:09.984
And what of justice?

345
00:35:10.067 --> 00:35:13.321
Of temperance?
Or is strength now to be our only god?

346
00:35:19.535 --> 00:35:20.828
So you cast me aside.

347
00:35:22.830 --> 00:35:24.165
Have I not spared you?

348
00:35:26.667 --> 00:35:29.879
What we must do now is terrible.

349
00:35:32.214 --> 00:35:33.716
Will you preside over it?

350
00:35:34.925 --> 00:35:37.386
- Is this who you are. Alicent?
- I did not ask to be spared.

351
00:35:41.974 --> 00:35:43.976
And I did not give you leave
to speak my name.

352
00:35:57.365 --> 00:35:58.991
Halt!

353
00:36:04.538 --> 00:36:05.581
Stay back!

354
00:36:07.208 --> 00:36:08.542
Get him out!

355
00:36:09.710 --> 00:36:10.920
Somebody get him!

356
00:36:12.254 --> 00:36:16.133
Stay back!
No! Hold fast! Hold fast!

357
00:36:16.801 --> 00:36:19.428
Stay back! Halt!

358
00:36:24.266 --> 00:36:25.559
Back!

359
00:36:26.060 --> 00:36:28.854
Disperse! Disperse!

360
00:36:30.064 --> 00:36:35.444
By order of Aemond Targaryen.
Prince Regent and Protector of the Realm!

361
00:36:35.528 --> 00:36:37.822
- Aemond?
- Does he mean the king?

362
00:36:37.905 --> 00:36:40.241
- I don't know.
- You cannot keep us here!

363
00:36:40.324 --> 00:36:42.159
You are ordered to return to your homes!

364
00:36:42.243 --> 00:36:43.327
We want meat!

365
00:36:43.411 --> 00:36:44.787
- Meat!
- Meat!

366
00:37:04.390 --> 00:37:07.101
Our Lord Grover Tully
has not declared for Rhaenyra.

367
00:37:08.936 --> 00:37:11.021
It means death to bare steel
against your liege.

368
00:37:11.105 --> 00:37:12.648
as I'm sure my prince is aware.

369
00:37:14.859 --> 00:37:16.277
And against your queen?

370
00:37:19.196 --> 00:37:20.196
Hm?

371
00:37:25.536 --> 00:37:27.705
Jason Lannister is marshaling to the west.

372
00:37:28.831 --> 00:37:30.875
We need to check him
before he reaches Riverrun.

373
00:37:31.876 --> 00:37:33.210
That requires passage.

374
00:37:33.878 --> 00:37:37.256
And if Stark's army's too slow?
The wind's rising.

375
00:37:38.048 --> 00:37:39.717
Winter is nigh upon us.

376
00:37:39.800 --> 00:37:43.471
Our hesitance does not lie
in Rhaenyra as queen.

377
00:37:43.554 --> 00:37:46.515
nor in the ruminations
of Lord Tully. the oaf.

378
00:37:47.808 --> 00:37:49.518
Our fear lies in Vhagar.

379
00:37:50.269 --> 00:37:56.358
You fear a dragon leagues away
when mine own sits outside your walls?

380
00:38:00.696 --> 00:38:03.949
- Do you offer us your protection?
- I do.

381
00:38:10.748 --> 00:38:12.583
And the protection of my uncle.

382
00:38:13.959 --> 00:38:18.047
And Daemon. I'm sure.
has consented to this?

383
00:38:18.130 --> 00:38:20.174
He will do as his queen commands.

384
00:38:20.257 --> 00:38:23.052
That does lend us some comfort.
though it occurs to me

385
00:38:23.135 --> 00:38:25.179
that dragons cannot be
in two places at once.

386
00:38:25.262 --> 00:38:26.263
Or three.

387
00:38:29.808 --> 00:38:30.809
What do you want?

388
00:38:33.979 --> 00:38:37.107
Larys Strong has been relieved
of his castle.

389
00:38:37.983 --> 00:38:40.945
Does the queen intend
to raise up a new lord?

390
00:38:45.407 --> 00:38:46.825
You want Harrenhal.

391
00:39:05.844 --> 00:39:09.557
For that. my mother will want
more than your crossing.

392
00:39:12.476 --> 00:39:14.103
What does Her Grace desire?

393
00:39:17.147 --> 00:39:18.691
Bent knees.

394
00:39:50.264 --> 00:39:53.559
<i>No! No! No!</i>

395
00:39:53.642 --> 00:39:57.062
<i>No! No! No!</i>

396
00:40:13.120 --> 00:40:14.121
Up.

397
00:40:15.581 --> 00:40:19.209
You were born to wield a sword.
but not so much an ax. perhaps.

398
00:40:21.045 --> 00:40:22.765
There are others
who would sit idle

399
00:40:22.796 --> 00:40:24.923
and wait for their claims
to be brought to them.

400
00:40:25.007 --> 00:40:27.176
- That is not my way.
- Does splitting firewood justify

401
00:40:27.259 --> 00:40:28.385
what's followed you here?

402
00:40:28.469 --> 00:40:32.681
Let it not be said that Daemon Targaryen
failed to dirty his hands in this war.

403
00:40:32.765 --> 00:40:33.932
Oh. let me see them.

404
00:40:35.684 --> 00:40:37.478
- Sit.
- Ah.

405
00:40:37.561 --> 00:40:38.604
Sit!

406
00:40:43.817 --> 00:40:48.989
I hear strange things from Bracken land.
from Stone Hedge and Lambswold and Mory.

407
00:40:50.074 --> 00:40:51.325
There's news. then?

408
00:40:52.159 --> 00:40:53.285
News?

409
00:40:54.536 --> 00:40:55.537
No.

410
00:40:57.790 --> 00:40:59.708
What I hear.
I hear in the wind.

411
00:41:01.752 --> 00:41:03.003
Cries of anguish.

412
00:41:05.464 --> 00:41:09.134
Children being taken from their mothers.
men coming home

413
00:41:09.218 --> 00:41:12.888
to find their doors unlatched.
their wives carried away.

414
00:41:15.891 --> 00:41:17.309
War is a terrible thing.

415
00:41:18.686 --> 00:41:19.937
This is not war.

416
00:41:21.438 --> 00:41:26.151
These are crimes against the innocent.
that any upright man would repudiate.

417
00:41:26.235 --> 00:41:29.029
Surely you haven't mistaken me
for an upright man.

418
00:41:30.739 --> 00:41:33.659
The Brackens had their chance
to do as I required.

419
00:41:34.368 --> 00:41:36.453
They will perhaps think better
of their decision

420
00:41:36.537 --> 00:41:38.789
if their children's lives
are staked on it.

421
00:41:41.125 --> 00:41:43.210
Is that the kind of army you would raise?

422
00:41:44.420 --> 00:41:48.882
Men who hate you.
who serve you under duress?

423
00:41:48.966 --> 00:41:51.218
Once they agree to serve me.
I'll treat them fairly.

424
00:41:52.094 --> 00:41:55.347
Set an example for the rest
of the Riverlands to follow.

425
00:41:55.431 --> 00:41:57.975
And once again. in the name of power.

426
00:41:58.058 --> 00:42:00.728
it's the weak and the women
who must endure.

427
00:42:03.522 --> 00:42:06.024
That fool Aegon is unlike to survive.

428
00:42:08.485 --> 00:42:10.779
The realm will suffer
if Aemond One-Eye rules.

429
00:42:12.364 --> 00:42:13.866
You should pray you never meet him.

430
00:42:14.700 --> 00:42:16.910
He will cut you down
soon as wish you good day.

431
00:42:16.994 --> 00:42:19.556
I'd heard the same thing about you.
But I'll cross you no further.

432
00:42:19.580 --> 00:42:22.541
I'm sure your tactics are.
after all. approved by the queen.

433
00:42:28.505 --> 00:42:30.048
She cannot succeed. Alys.

434
00:42:31.341 --> 00:42:33.343
Even if I willed it to be so.

435
00:42:33.427 --> 00:42:35.721
The people who support her
will not be led by her.

436
00:42:35.804 --> 00:42:37.765
They look to a man for strength.

437
00:42:37.848 --> 00:42:41.310
Who's better suited to it.
the Hightowers with their scheming.

438
00:42:41.393 --> 00:42:43.228
or Viserys' first true heir?

439
00:42:44.897 --> 00:42:48.817
When I take King's Landing.
Rhaenyra is welcome to join me there

440
00:42:48.901 --> 00:42:50.694
and take her place by my side.

441
00:42:51.361 --> 00:42:54.740
King and queen. ruling together.

442
00:42:55.991 --> 00:42:57.534
And if you lose?

443
00:42:57.618 --> 00:43:00.370
Then I'll be dead.
And none of this will be my problem.

444
00:43:01.079 --> 00:43:04.249
It's a pity. don't you think.
that you never knew your mother?

445
00:43:07.920 --> 00:43:10.005
A message. Your Grace.

446
00:43:11.673 --> 00:43:12.758
Uh...

447
00:43:15.177 --> 00:43:17.930
Uh. fresh news from Stone Hedge.

448
00:43:18.013 --> 00:43:20.349
The Blackwoods have overwhelmed
the Brackens.

449
00:43:20.432 --> 00:43:23.602
and. uh. Lord Amos has pledged
his banner to you.

450
00:43:23.685 --> 00:43:25.521
House Bracken is yours.

451
00:43:27.731 --> 00:43:30.317
Call Ser Willem here
so that I might congratulate him.

452
00:43:30.400 --> 00:43:33.028
The Blackwoods will be feted
in these halls.

453
00:43:44.873 --> 00:43:46.458
I sought you at High Tide.

454
00:43:47.543 --> 00:43:49.878
I was surprised
when they said you were here.

455
00:43:51.004 --> 00:43:52.381
My castle is a tomb.

456
00:43:54.383 --> 00:43:56.552
Empty. Haunted.

457
00:43:57.469 --> 00:43:59.888
I am sad to have missed its highest days.

458
00:44:01.348 --> 00:44:05.018
I imagine your Hall of Nine filled
with lords and kings.

459
00:44:05.102 --> 00:44:08.146
all eager to treat
with the legendary Lord of the Tides.

460
00:44:09.982 --> 00:44:15.320
The wealth you brought back from Yi Ti
and Asshai inspiring awe and envy.

461
00:44:18.156 --> 00:44:20.158
I wonder if any of them knew
it was all for her.

462
00:44:29.459 --> 00:44:31.628
Queen Rhaenyra wishes to name you Hand.

463
00:44:35.048 --> 00:44:37.885
Even the death of my wife
does not content her.

464
00:44:41.138 --> 00:44:42.931
Has she not asked enough of my house?

465
00:44:43.891 --> 00:44:45.851
It is a sign of her great esteem.

466
00:44:47.769 --> 00:44:50.647
Or does she think the position
will compensate me for my loss?

467
00:44:52.190 --> 00:44:56.361
Pledge your peace to King's Landing. then.
They will accept it most gleefully.

468
00:44:59.448 --> 00:45:01.742
Rather I would sail into the west
and be lost.

469
00:45:03.201 --> 00:45:07.581
You have done so before. at great cost
to yourself and those who loved you.

470
00:45:10.626 --> 00:45:12.753
Rhaenys was not only your wife.

471
00:45:13.921 --> 00:45:16.256
Not a thing to be taken from you.

472
00:45:17.174 --> 00:45:21.803
She was a Targaryen princess.
the Queen Who Never Was.

473
00:45:21.887 --> 00:45:25.390
and she flew to Rook's Rest
of her own will in defense of her kin.

474
00:45:25.474 --> 00:45:26.892
And she died.

475
00:45:26.975 --> 00:45:29.061
She died as she would have wished to die.

476
00:45:29.770 --> 00:45:34.650
With honor. in dragonfire.
The way my mother chose.

477
00:45:36.944 --> 00:45:39.363
And the way I myself wish to meet my end.

478
00:45:47.037 --> 00:45:49.289
I grieve my grandmother who loved me.

479
00:45:50.165 --> 00:45:51.959
But I carry her on with me.

480
00:45:53.710 --> 00:45:56.254
I will see Rhaenyra
ascend the Iron Throne.

481
00:45:56.338 --> 00:45:57.589
as Rhaenys wished.

482
00:45:58.548 --> 00:46:00.384
As Rhaenys herself should have.

483
00:46:03.303 --> 00:46:05.514
You yourself may do as you see fit.

484
00:46:09.559 --> 00:46:10.560
Granddaughter.

485
00:46:18.694 --> 00:46:20.821
I would make you my heir.

486
00:46:23.323 --> 00:46:24.741
I am blood and fire.

487
00:46:25.993 --> 00:46:28.161
Driftmark must pass to salt and sea.

488
00:46:47.639 --> 00:46:48.682
Your Grace.

489
00:46:52.602 --> 00:46:53.895
You were correct...

490
00:46:55.439 --> 00:46:57.691
in saying our best hope of an army
is with Daemon.

491
00:47:00.986 --> 00:47:05.615
And I have perhaps erred
in waiting for him to prove himself.

492
00:47:08.326 --> 00:47:09.870
I wish you to go to Harrenhal.

493
00:47:12.080 --> 00:47:14.458
Are you removing me from your council?

494
00:47:16.084 --> 00:47:17.085
Ser Alfred...

495
00:47:18.712 --> 00:47:21.798
I... I will not deny you have tried
my patience of late.

496
00:47:21.882 --> 00:47:25.552
Or that I would prefer a council
more inclined to champion their queen.

497
00:47:25.635 --> 00:47:30.807
but... you and your house
served my father well.

498
00:47:31.850 --> 00:47:34.936
And I know you will never accept
the Hightower claim.

499
00:47:36.605 --> 00:47:38.899
Not while I live. Your Grace.

500
00:47:42.069 --> 00:47:45.864
We cannot challenge King's Landing
without the Riverlands.

501
00:47:45.947 --> 00:47:49.117
But I will not send a message by raven
for Daemon to disregard.

502
00:47:51.995 --> 00:47:53.663
I ask you to...

503
00:47:55.832 --> 00:47:56.833
reason with him.

504
00:47:58.126 --> 00:48:02.172
Find out his state of mind
and his intentions.

505
00:48:04.674 --> 00:48:06.093
Intentions?

506
00:48:07.219 --> 00:48:09.805
Whether he means to raise
a host for me or for himself.

507
00:48:13.850 --> 00:48:15.018
He would not dare.

508
00:48:15.102 --> 00:48:17.479
Have you known Daemon
to lack in daring?

509
00:48:19.356 --> 00:48:22.901
Go now with haste.
I'll send good men to see to your safety.

510
00:48:31.326 --> 00:48:33.411
Have you any message for him?

511
00:48:37.958 --> 00:48:40.669
Tell him I would much like to finish
our last conversation.

512
00:48:43.630 --> 00:48:44.631
Your Grace.

513
00:49:21.251 --> 00:49:22.252
Your Grace.

514
00:49:26.464 --> 00:49:30.177
What is it. Ser Simon?
Is the pudding now served?

515
00:49:31.136 --> 00:49:33.680
The Riverlords have come. Your Grace.

516
00:49:33.763 --> 00:49:35.891
- They wish an audience.
- Now?

517
00:49:37.225 --> 00:49:39.603
- What godless hour is it?
- The wolf.

518
00:49:40.520 --> 00:49:42.189
They are demanding to speak presently.

519
00:50:13.178 --> 00:50:15.972
I see I must begin here
with a lesson in etiquette.

520
00:50:16.723 --> 00:50:19.476
Or failing that. in proper fear
of your Targaryen master.

521
00:50:21.603 --> 00:50:25.857
Is there some reason you feel free
to wake a king in his bed?

522
00:50:26.816 --> 00:50:28.735
Or shall I now begin your education?

523
00:50:29.361 --> 00:50:33.865
House Bracken have been brought to heel
at the hands of Willem Blackwood.

524
00:50:34.658 --> 00:50:35.992
That news is stale.

525
00:50:36.743 --> 00:50:39.955
Yes. but there have been.
um. complications.

526
00:50:40.038 --> 00:50:44.209
The sacred septs on Bracken lands
were looted and burned.

527
00:50:44.292 --> 00:50:45.752
As were the fields and farms.

528
00:50:45.835 --> 00:50:49.005
The livestock were stolen
and our peasants put to the sword.

529
00:50:49.089 --> 00:50:53.134
They pursued the women and the children.
There were works of barbarity.

530
00:50:53.218 --> 00:50:58.390
Punishing Bracken for his own treasons
is one thing. aye. But these other acts...

531
00:50:58.473 --> 00:51:01.059
The Brackens were given their chance.
They would not see reason.

532
00:51:01.142 --> 00:51:03.311
The Blackwoods have exploited the war
for the crown

533
00:51:03.395 --> 00:51:05.272
to visit atrocities upon their old rivals.

534
00:51:05.355 --> 00:51:08.775
I have seen my share of their quarrels.
There is no honor in a fight such as this!

535
00:51:08.858 --> 00:51:10.443
Honor? What of common decency?

536
00:51:10.527 --> 00:51:14.447
These beasts proudly carried the banner
of House Targaryen.

537
00:51:14.531 --> 00:51:16.324
Red dragon on black.

538
00:51:22.622 --> 00:51:25.709
A terrible war is being fought
in these lands.

539
00:51:29.587 --> 00:51:31.506
Have you looked after our girls?

540
00:51:39.014 --> 00:51:42.642
We should have expected nothing more
from a man who ordered the slaughter

541
00:51:42.726 --> 00:51:44.769
of a child in his mother's arms.

542
00:51:47.063 --> 00:51:50.233
That is a lie. and I will have the man
who told it brought before me.

543
00:51:50.317 --> 00:51:54.279
Well. your man is half the kingdom.
my prince.

544
00:51:57.991 --> 00:51:59.659
Know this. interloper.

545
00:52:00.618 --> 00:52:03.455
The Riverlands are an ancient place.

546
00:52:03.538 --> 00:52:06.916
watched closely
by the eyes of old gods and new.

547
00:52:07.000 --> 00:52:08.543
And dragon or no.

548
00:52:09.377 --> 00:52:12.005
we shall not raise our banners
for a tyrant.

549
00:53:20.657 --> 00:53:21.866
Move along. lass.

550
00:53:21.950 --> 00:53:24.411
I have an errand for the lady Mysaria.

551
00:53:25.620 --> 00:53:26.871
I thought she was dead.

552
00:53:27.747 --> 00:53:29.499
Would she die without collecting her due?

553
00:53:31.709 --> 00:53:33.211
I must see an old friend.

554
00:53:35.255 --> 00:53:37.257
Most people want out these days.

555
00:54:22.427 --> 00:54:23.553
Elinda?

556
00:55:15.396 --> 00:55:16.856
Was it worth the price?

557
00:56:08.074 --> 00:56:09.701
Mummy...

558
00:56:27.343 --> 00:56:28.678
Prince Jacaerys. Your Grace.

559
00:56:53.453 --> 00:56:54.454
Visenya.

560
00:56:55.538 --> 00:56:57.749
Vhagar's first rider.

561
00:56:58.625 --> 00:57:00.877
And the first wielder of Dark Sister.

562
00:57:03.129 --> 00:57:05.009
I hope you do not mean
to use her as an example.

563
00:57:05.089 --> 00:57:06.382
Why shouldn't I?

564
00:57:07.342 --> 00:57:09.302
Well. it was a long time ago.

565
00:57:19.562 --> 00:57:21.356
What is the mood at the Twins?

566
00:57:23.441 --> 00:57:25.026
Did his lordship quibble?

567
00:57:28.196 --> 00:57:31.240
He wishes for the Freys
to be granted Harrenhal.

568
00:57:33.242 --> 00:57:34.869
At war's end. assuming.

569
00:57:38.373 --> 00:57:41.751
I'm proud of you. Jace.
You have done our cause a great service.

570
00:57:44.837 --> 00:57:46.839
Then why do you look angry?

571
00:57:56.015 --> 00:57:58.810
You chafed at being prevented from action.

572
00:57:58.893 --> 00:58:03.981
Imagine my lot. I'm a dragonrider as well.
with a war being fought over my ascension.

573
00:58:05.775 --> 00:58:09.862
And yet. I must wait here. always prudent.

574
00:58:11.197 --> 00:58:14.367
sending others to fight
and be felled in my name.

575
00:58:15.284 --> 00:58:17.203
Even you have managed to do your part.

576
00:58:18.329 --> 00:58:22.875
You are the queen. The tie that binds us.
No harm can come to you.

577
00:58:22.959 --> 00:58:25.253
And you are my son.
and I did not give you leave to go.

578
00:58:27.630 --> 00:58:29.674
You do not give me leave
to go to anything.

579
00:58:30.508 --> 00:58:34.053
But who else is there? Rhaenys is dead.
and Baela cannot bear the burden alone.

580
00:58:34.137 --> 00:58:36.431
And when Aemond comes hunting for you?

581
00:58:36.514 --> 00:58:40.727
Your dragon is young.
Will you fly before Vhagar as Luke did?

582
00:58:47.859 --> 00:58:49.235
Perhaps Daemon could...

583
00:58:53.156 --> 00:58:54.490
Daemon is not here.

584
00:58:55.992 --> 00:58:58.077
And Aemond now rules in King's Landing.

585
00:58:59.704 --> 00:59:01.080
Is Aegon dead?

586
00:59:01.164 --> 00:59:03.207
Dead or alive.
we have no answer for Vhagar.

587
00:59:03.833 --> 00:59:06.544
Aemond will not wait long
to press his advantage. And then what?

588
00:59:09.547 --> 00:59:13.760
I have done all I can from here.
Sent my messages. invoked my alliances.

589
00:59:14.343 --> 00:59:17.138
But if all else fails.
it is I who must fight.

590
00:59:18.264 --> 00:59:21.392
Vhagar is big. but Syrax is quicker.

591
00:59:21.476 --> 00:59:22.602
So was Meleys.

592
00:59:22.685 --> 00:59:25.730
Meleys fought two dragons.
and one of them is slain.

593
00:59:27.815 --> 00:59:31.068
Shall I fight for my birthright or shall I
wait here until we are all destroyed?

594
00:59:37.492 --> 00:59:38.701
I need dragons.

595
00:59:42.914 --> 00:59:45.750
We have no dearth of dragons.

596
00:59:46.667 --> 00:59:49.045
We have two large enough
to stand against Vhagar.

597
00:59:49.754 --> 00:59:52.215
They are called Vermithor and Silverwing.

598
00:59:53.090 --> 00:59:54.467
And they sleep beneath our feet.

599
00:59:54.550 --> 00:59:57.178
Yes. and if only they had riders.
none could stand against me.

600
00:59:58.471 --> 01:00:01.474
I would go forth in strength
and not from necessity.

601
01:00:03.142 --> 01:00:04.560
There is Rhaena.

602
01:00:04.644 --> 01:00:07.313
Who nearly lost her life
in her last attempt.

603
01:00:08.940 --> 01:00:10.483
I would not risk it again.

604
01:00:17.073 --> 01:00:19.742
There are those of our line
who never ruled.

605
01:00:20.910 --> 01:00:23.704
Those who married into other noble houses.

606
01:00:24.455 --> 01:00:27.250
their children born with other names.

607
01:00:27.333 --> 01:00:30.837
A generation ago or more.
The blood would be thin.

608
01:00:30.920 --> 01:00:32.046
And yet...

609
01:00:33.798 --> 01:00:38.928
A dragon will only accept a dragonlord
to ride it. Or so say the histories.

610
01:00:39.011 --> 01:00:43.808
Valyrian histories.
Written to gild us in glory.

611
01:00:46.769 --> 01:00:51.107
Are you suggesting we put a Mallister
on a dragon? A Tarly?

612
01:00:51.190 --> 01:00:52.733
It's better than death and defeat.

613
01:00:59.490 --> 01:01:02.785
There are records here. surely.
of our line

614
01:01:02.869 --> 01:01:04.662
and of those who fell out of it.

615
01:01:12.670 --> 01:01:14.297
There could be scores of them.

616
01:01:21.888 --> 01:01:23.180
It's a mad thought.
